<body lang=EN-US>

    <div class=WordSection1>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <b>
                <span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Eligibility to Donate Blood</span>
            </b>
        </p>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <b>
                <span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Basic Requirements</span>
            </b>
        </p>

        <ul type=disc>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Be at least 17 years old in most
                    states
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Weight: At least 45 kg (100 Ibs)
                    for both males and females
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Well Being:&nbsp;Feeling well that
                    day. Not having colds, coughs or flu in the last one week. No fever
                    (Temperature &gt;37.5°C) in the last 3 weeks.
                </span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <b>
                <span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Major Illness/Surgery</span>
            </b>
        </p>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                Persons with the following conditions
                are&nbsp;<b>not eligible</b> for blood donation:
            </span>
        </p>

        <ul type=disc>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Diseases of the heart or lungs
                    (Donors who are asthmatic and without symptoms of asthma is eligible)
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>High blood pressure on medication</span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Diabetes on medication</span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Major surgery (can donate after 12
                    months)
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    AIDS or symptoms of AIDS, such as
                    unexplained fevers, severe night sweats, unexpected weight loss, swollen
                    glands, chronic diarrhoea or rare cancer
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Epilepsy</span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Hepatitis B or C</span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Syphilis</span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <b>
                <span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Some Common Reasons For Temporary
                    Deferral
                </span>
            </b>
        </p>

        <ul type=disc>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Cold, flu or sore throat, please
                    wait&nbsp;<b>one week</b> after recovery or treatment
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Tooth extraction or dental work,
                    please wait&nbsp;<b>3 days</b> after treatment
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Skin infections (minor), wait&nbsp;<b>
                        1
                        week
                    </b> after complete healing
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Normal pregnancy, please wait&nbsp;<b>
                        6
                        weeks
                    </b> after delivery and when you are not breast-feeding.
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Travelled to a malaria endemic area
                    such as rural areas in Malaysia, Thailand, Indonesia, Philippines, India,
                    etc, please wait&nbsp;<b>6 weeks to 3 years</b> and ask the attending
                    doctor/nurse whether you are eligible for donation
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Close contact with Hepatitis B,
                    wait&nbsp;<b>12 months</b> and after full course of hepatitis B
                    vaccination (and shown a satisfactory antibody response)
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
                <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
     font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                    Infectious Diseases e.g.
                    Chickenpox, Measles, Dengue, wait&nbsp;<b>6 months</b> after recovery
                </span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <b>
                <span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>Medication</span>
            </b>
        </p>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>
                People who are taking drugs for cancer
                treatment, heart diseases, high blood pressure, diabetes or current infections
                will not be accepted as blood donors.
            </span>
        </p>

        <p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:normal'>
            <span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'>For those taking:</span>
        </p>

